n          \"issueNumber\": \"2\",\n          \"name\": \"2\",\n          \"url\": \"https:\/\/journals.sagepub.com\/toc\/esta\/28\/2\",\n          \"datePublished\": \"2025-05\",\n          \"isPartOf\": {\n            \"@id\": \"https:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/publications\/reviews\/cosmic-connections\/#volume\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"@id\": \"https:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/publications\/reviews\/cosmic-connections\/#review\",\n          \"@type\": [\n            \"ScholarlyArticle\",\n            \"Review\"\n          ],\n          \"url\": \"https:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/publications\/reviews\/cosmic-connections\/\",\n          \"mainEntityOfPage\": {\n            \"@id\": \"https:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/publications\/reviews\/cosmic-connections\/#webpage\"\n          },\n          \"headline\": \"Review of Cosmic Connections\",\n          \"name\": \"Review of Cosmic Connections\",\n          \"description\": \"In a book which bids fair to become his culminating output, Taylor joins up the facets of an extraordinary career.\",\n          \"version\": \"Author’s Original Manuscript\",\n          \"inLanguage\": \"en\",\n          \"author\": {\n            \"@id\": \"https:\/\/orcid.org\/0000-0002-2599-3227\"\n          },\n          \"itemReviewed\": {\n            \"@id\": \"https:\/\/doi.org\/10.4159\/9780674297074\"\n          },\n          \"isBasedOn\": {\n            \"@id\": \"https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1177\/13684310241249684\"\n          },\n          \"citation\": {\n            \"@id\": \"https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1177\/13684310241249684\"\n          },\n          \"datePublished\": \"2024-05-24T12:00:00+01:00\",\n          \"dateCreated\": \"2024-04-02T17:09:00+01:00\"\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n```\n\nHow is that looking?\n\nIt seems that the dateLabel value isn’t being used. For instance, based on something you said, I thought the idea was to use dateLabel as a name for the issue; for instance, the issue for Cosmic Connections would be called May 2025. Or did I misunderstand?\n\n> It is looking good overall. The main `firstPublishedOnline` distinction is now\n> being captured correctly for the **published DOI article**:\n> \n> ```json\n> {\n>   \"@id\": \"https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1177\/13684310241249684\",\n>   \"datePublished\": \"2024-05-24\",\n>   \"isPartOf\": {\n>     \"@id\":\n> \"https:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/publications\/reviews\/cosmic-connections\/#issue\"\n>   }\n> }\n> ```\n> \n> and the later issue assignment is now separately captured on the issue node:\n> \n> ```json\n> {\n>   \"@id\":\n> \"https:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/publications\/reviews\/cosmic-connections\/#issue\",\n>   \"@type\": \"PublicationIssue\",\n>   \"issueNumber\": \"2\",\n>   \"datePublished\": \"2025-05\"\n> }\n> ```\n> \n> That is the important conceptual distinction:\n> \n> ```text\n> DOI article datePublished → first online publication date, 24 May 2024\n> Issue datePublished       → issue month\/date, May 2025\n> ```\n> \n> So the core implementation is working.\n> \n> ## 1. Main thing to fix: local `#review` still has the old noon datetime\n> \n> The DOI article node is now correct:\n> \n> ```json\n> \"datePublished\": \"2024-05-24\"\n> ```\n> \n> But the local review node still has:\n> \n> ```json\n> \"datePublished\": \"2024-05-24T12:00:00+01:00\"\n> ```\n> \n> This is the main remaining inconsistency.\n> \n> Unless noon is meaningful and verified, change the local node too:\n> \n> ```json\n> \"datePublished\": \"2024-05-24\"\n> ```\n> \n> or, if you want to be especially precise about the local manuscript being\n> different from the DOI version, consider whether the local `#review` node should\n> have a different publication\/upload date at all. But if it is inheriting the\n> published review’s publication date, it should use the same date-only value:\n> \n> ```json\n> \"datePublished\": \"2024-05-24\"\n> ```\n> \n> So: **yes, fix that one.**\n> \n> ---\n> \n> ## 2. The DOI article \/ issue distinction is now right\n> \n> This part is good:\n> \n> ```json\n> {\n>   \"@id\": \"https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1177\/13684310241249684\",\n>   \"@type\": [\n>     \"ScholarlyArticle\",\n>     \"Review\"\n>   ],\n>   \"datePublished\": \"2024-05-24\",\n>   \"pagination\": \"339–42\",\n>   \"pageStart\": \"339\",\n>   \"pageEnd\": \"342\",\n>   \"isPartOf\": {\n>     \"@id\":\n> \"https:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/publications\/reviews\/cosmic-connections\/#issue\"\n>   }\n> }\n> ```\n> \n> and:\n> \n> ```json\n> {\n>   \"@id\":\n> \"https:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/publications\/reviews\/cosmic-connections\/#issue\",\n>   \"@type\": \"PublicationIssue\",\n>   \"issueNumber\": \"2\",\n>   \"datePublished\": \"2025-05\",\n>   \"isPartOf\": {\n>     \"@id\":\n> \"https:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/publications\/reviews\/cosmic-connections\/#volume\"\n>   }\n> }\n> ```\n> \n> That says:\n> \n> > The review was first published online on 24 May 2024, then appeared in\n> European Journal of Social Theory, volume 28, issue 2, May 2025, pages 339–42.\n> \n> That is exactly the metadata distinction you were aiming for.\n> \n> ---\n> \n> ## 3. About `dateLabel`: you did not exactly misunderstand, but I would handle\n> it carefully\n> \n> There is no standard Schema.org property called:\n> \n> ```json\n> \"dateLabel\"\n> ```\n> \n> So I would not emit this directly into JSON-LD.\n> \n> When I mentioned something like `issueDateLabel`, I meant it as an\n> **internal\/frontmatter helper field** if you need a human-readable label such\n> as:\n> \n> ```text\n> May 2025\n> ```\n> \n> It can be useful for visible display, but it does not have to appear in JSON-LD.\n> \n> For JSON-LD, this is already enough:\n> \n> ```json\n> \"datePublished\": \"2025-05\"\n> ```\n> \n> A consumer can interpret that as May 2025.\n> \n> ---\n> \n> ## 4. Should `dateLabel` become the issue `name`?\n> \n> Possibly, but not necessarily.\n> \n> Right now you have:\n> \n> ```json\n> \"name\": \"2\"\n> ```\n> \n> on the issue node:\n> \n> ```json\n> {\n>   \"@id\":\n> \"https:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/publications\/reviews\/cosmic-connections\/#issue\",\n>   \"@type\": \"PublicationIssue\",\n>   \"issueNumber\": \"2\",\n>   \"name\": \"2\",\n>   \"url\": \"https:\/\/journals.sagepub.com\/toc\/esta\/28\/2\",\n>   \"datePublished\": \"2025-05\"\n> }\n> ```\n> \n> I would not keep:\n> \n> ```json\n> \"name\": \"2\"\n> ```\n> \n> It is redundant with:\n> \n> ```json\n> \"issueNumber\": \"2\"\n> ```\n> \n> and is not a meaningful name.\n> \n> You have three sensible options.\n> \n> ---\n> \n> ### Option A: omit `name` from ordinary issue nodes\n> \n> This is the simplest and probably best default:\n> \n> ```json\n> {\n>   \"@id\":\n> \"https:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/publications\/reviews\/cosmic-connections\/#issue\",\n>   \"@type\": \"PublicationIssue\",\n>   \"issueNumber\": \"2\",\n>   \"url\": \"https:\/\/journals.sagepub.com\/toc\/esta\/28\/2\",\n>   \"datePublished\": \"2025-05\",\n>   \"isPartOf\": {\n>     \"@id\":\n> \"https:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/publications\/reviews\/cosmic-connections\/#volume\"\n>   }\n> }\n> ```\n> \n> This is fully adequate.\n> \n> ---\n> \n> ### Option B: use a fuller generated issue name\n> \n> If you want an issue `name`, make it descriptive rather than just `\"2\"`:\n> \n> ```json\n> \"name\": \"European Journal of Social Theory, Volume 28, Issue 2, May 2025\"\n> ```\n> \n> This is clear and useful.\n> \n> This could be generated from:\n> \n> ```yaml\n> periodical.name: \"European Journal of Social Theory\"\n> volume: \"28\"\n> issue: \"2\"\n> issueDatePublished: \"2025-05\"\n> ```\n> \n> or from an explicit internal label:\n> \n> ```yaml\n> issueDateLabel: \"May 2025\"\n> ```\n> \n> Then generate:\n> \n> ```ts\n> issue.name = `${periodical.name}, Volume ${volume}, Issue ${issue},\n> ${issueDateLabel}`;\n> ```\n> \n> ---\n> \n> ### Option C: use `issueDateLabel` alone as issue `name`\n> \n> You could set:\n> \n> ```json\n> \"name\": \"May 2025\"\n> ```\n> \n> But I think this is less good than Option B, because “May 2025” is a date label,\n> not really the name of the issue. It is acceptable if the publisher prominently\n> presents the issue that way, but it is not as identifying as:\n> \n> ```text\n> European Journal of Social Theory, Volume 28, Issue 2, May 2025\n> ```\n> \n> ---\n> \n> ## 5. Recommended rule for your project\n> \n> I would adopt this rule:\n> \n> ```text\n> issueDatePublished\n>   Internal\/frontmatter field containing the machine-readable issue date,\n>   e.g. 2025-05.\n> \n> issueDateLabel\n>   Optional internal\/frontmatter field for display wording, e.g. May 2025.\n>   Do not emit as dateLabel in JSON-LD.\n> \n> PublicationIssue.datePublished\n>   Generated from issueDatePublished.\n> \n> PublicationIssue.name\n>   Omit by default unless an explicit issue name\/title\/label is useful.\n>   If present, prefer a descriptive label such as:\n>   \"European Journal of Social Theory, Volume 28, Issue 2, May 2025\".\n> ```\n> \n> So for Cosmic Connections, I would either emit no issue `name`, or emit:\n> \n> ```json\n> \"name\": \"European Journal of Social Theory, Volume 28, Issue 2, May 2025\"\n> ```\n> \n> I would not emit:\n> \n> ```json\n> \"name\": \"2\"\n> ```\n> \n> ---\n> \n> ## 6. Check whether `image` on the DOI article is really article image or issue\n> cover\n> \n> You currently have this on the DOI article node:\n> \n> ```json\n> \"image\":\n> \"https:\/\/journals.sagepub.com\/cms\/asset\/e55d45ab-8419-4908-b935-0563c55874fa\/\n> esta_28_2.cover.png\"\n> ```\n> \n> That appears to be an **issue cover**, not an article-specific image.\n> \n> This is not a serious problem, but if you want the model to be cleaner, move it\n> to the `PublicationIssue` node:\n> \n> ```json\n> {\n>   \"@id\":\n> \"https:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/publications\/reviews\/cosmic-connections\/#issue\",\n>   \"@type\": \"PublicationIssue\",\n>   \"image\":\n> \"https:\/\/journals.sagepub.com\/cms\/asset\/e55d45ab-8419-4908-b935-0563c55874fa\/\n> esta_28_2.cover.png\"\n> }\n> ```\n> \n> For Christian Right, you already put the issue cover on the issue node, which is\n> cleaner.\n> \n> So I would consider moving the Cosmic Connections cover image from the DOI\n> article node to the issue node.\n> \n> ---\n> \n> ## 7. `sameAs` and `url` are acceptable\n> \n> This is okay:\n> \n> ```json\n> \"url\": \"https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1177\/13684310241249684\",\n> \"sameAs\": [\n>   \"https:\/\/journals.sagepub.com\/doi\/10.1177\/13684310241249684\"\n> ]\n> ```\n> \n> As before, you could alternatively use the publisher landing page as `url` and\n> DOI as `@id`\/identifier, but the current model is acceptable.\n> \n> ---\n> \n> ## 8. `version: \"Author’s Original Manuscript\"` looks good\n> \n> This is important for Cosmic Connections:\n> \n> ```json\n> \"version\": \"Author’s Original Manuscript\"\n> ```\n> \n> and:\n> \n> ```json\n> \"isBasedOn\": {\n>   \"@id\": \"https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1177\/13684310241249684\"\n> },\n> \"citation\": {\n>   \"@id\": \"https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1177\/13684310241249684\"\n> }\n> ```\n> \n> This preserves the key rule that the local hosted version is materially\n> different from the published DOI version and should not use `sameAs`.\n> \n> That remains good.\n> \n> ---\n> \n> ## Recommended immediate changes\n> \n> I would make these small changes before calling the `firstPublishedOnline` work\n> complete for Cosmic Connections:\n> \n> 1. Change local `#review` date:\n> \n>    ```json\n>    \"datePublished\": \"2024-05-24T12:00:00+01:00\"\n>    ```\n> \n>    to:\n> \n>    ```json\n>    \"datePublished\": \"2024-05-24\"\n>    ```\n> \n> 2. Remove this from the issue node:\n> \n>    ```json\n>    \"name\": \"2\"\n>    ```\n> \n>    or replace it with:\n> \n>    ```json\n>    \"name\": \"European Journal of Social Theory, Volume 28, Issue 2, May 2025\"\n>    ```\n> \n> 3. Consider moving the SAGE cover image from the DOI article node to the issue\n> node.\n> \n> The core structure is good. The date distinction is working. The `dateLabel`\n> field should be treated as an internal display\/helper field, not as a direct\n> Schema.org property; if used in JSON-LD at all, use it to help construct a\n> meaningful `PublicationIssue.name`, not as a standalone `dateLabel`.\n\n26 May 2026 at 16:57:11 BST\n\n# JSON-LD and moving on\n\nThis is now the JSON-LD from the \/publications\/ page\n\n```json\n{\n      \"@context\": \"https:\/\/schema.org\",\n      \"@graph\": [\n        {\n          \"@id\": \"https:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/#website\",\n          \"@type\": \"WebSite\",\n          \"url\": \"https:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/\",\n          \"name\": \"Stevan Veljkovic\",\n          \"inLanguage\": \"en-GB\",\n          \"publisher\": {\n            \"@id\": \"https:\/\/orcid.org\/0000-0002-2599-3227\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"@id\": \"https:\/\/orcid.org\/0000-0002-2599-3227\",\n          \"@type\": \"Person\",\n          \"name\": \"Stevan Veljkovic\",\n          \"url\": \"https:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/\",\n          \"identifier\": {\n            \"@type\": \"PropertyValue\",\n            \"propertyID\": \"ORCID\",\n            \"value\": \"0000-0002-2599-3227\",\n            \"url\": \"https:\/\/orcid.org\/0000-0002-2599-3227\"\n          },\n          \"sameAs\": [\n            \"https:\/\/orcid.org\/0000-0002-2599-3227\",\n            \"https:\/\/scholar.google.com\/citations?user=e42TN4UAAAAJ\",\n            \"https:\/\/github.com\/smveljkovic\"\n          ]\n        },\n        {\n          \"@id\": \"https:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/publications\/\",\n          \"@type\": \"CollectionPage\",\n          \"url\": \"https:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/publications\/\",\n          \"name\": \"Publications | Dr Stevan Veljkovic\",\n          \"description\": \"Publications of Dr Stevan Veljkovic.\",\n          \"inLanguage\": \"en-GB\",\n          \"isPartOf\": {\n            \"@id\": \"https:\/\/stevanveljkov