t org-mode task can be marked as materially done.\n\n---\n\n## 2. One thing I would fix before moving on: article ID consistency\n\nOn `\/publications\/`, the Christian Right DOI node has both DOI and article ID:\n\n```json\n\"identifier\": [\n  {\n    \"@type\": \"PropertyValue\",\n    \"propertyID\": \"DOI\",\n    \"value\": \"10.1093\/jcs\/csaf039\",\n    \"url\": \"https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1093\/jcs\/csaf039\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"@type\": \"PropertyValue\",\n    \"propertyID\": \"Article ID\",\n    \"value\": \"csaf039\"\n  }\n]\n```\n\nBut on the Christian Right review page, the DOI review node only has the DOI identifier:\n\n```json\n\"identifier\": {\n  \"@type\": \"PropertyValue\",\n  \"propertyID\": \"DOI\",\n  \"value\": \"10.1093\/jcs\/csaf039\"\n}\n```\n\nI would make the review page match the publications page by adding the article ID there too:\n\n```json\n\"identifier\": [\n  {\n    \"@type\": \"PropertyValue\",\n    \"propertyID\": \"DOI\",\n    \"value\": \"10.1093\/jcs\/csaf039\",\n    \"url\": \"https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1093\/jcs\/csaf039\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"@type\": \"PropertyValue\",\n    \"propertyID\": \"Article ID\",\n    \"value\": \"csaf039\"\n  }\n]\n```\n\nThis is not strictly a periodical\/volume\/issue problem, but since `csaf039` is part of the journal article’s container-style metadata, I would do this quick consistency fix now.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Check `datePublished` on `PublicationIssue`\n\nBoth blocks still have:\n\n```json\n\"datePublished\": \"2025-07-01\"\n```\n\nfor the Christian Right issue.\n\nThis is fine **only if** `2025-07-01` is a verified issue publication date.\n\nIf you only know that it is the July 2025 issue, prefer:\n\n```json\n\"datePublished\": \"2025-07\"\n```\n\nor omit issue-level `datePublished`.\n\nBecause your next task is **`firstPublishedOnline`**, it may be sensible to leave this for the date\/refinement pass, but it should not remain an invented exact day if the exact day is not verified.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `\/publications\/` page title\/name still uses the old “Dr” style\n\nThis node says:\n\n```json\n\"name\": \"Publications | Dr Stevan Veljkovic\",\n\"description\": \"Publications of Dr Stevan Veljkovic.\"\n```\n\nand the `ItemList` says:\n\n```json\n\"name\": \"Publications of Dr Stevan Veljkovic\"\n```\n\nThis conflicts slightly with the adopted site-title\/name direction:\n\n```text\nWebSite.name \/ Person.name \/ og:site_name → Stevan Veljkovic\nordinary page title → Publications | Stevan Veljkovic\nsemantic page\/list name → Publications\n```\n\nI would eventually change these to something like:\n\n```json\n\"name\": \"Publications\",\n\"description\": \"Publications of Stevan Veljkovic.\"\n```\n\nand:\n\n```json\n\"name\": \"Publications of Stevan Veljkovic\"\n```\n\nThis is not part of the periodical\/volume\/issue task, so it does **not** block moving on. But it is a metadata cleanup item.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `\/publications\/` has some date precision issues unrelated to periodical nodes\n\nThis one stands out:\n\n```json\n\"datePublished\": \"2024-05-24T12:00:00+01:00\"\n```\n\nfor Cosmic Connections.\n\nUnless noon on 24 May 2024 is a real and meaningful publication time, this should become:\n\n```json\n\"datePublished\": \"2024-05-24\"\n```\n\nAlso check these:\n\n```json\n\"datePublished\": \"2025-01-01\"\n```\n\nand:\n\n```json\n\"datePublished\": \"2023-01-01\"\n```\n\nIf those are just year-level dates, avoid inventing 1 January. Use the exact date if known, a reduced date if acceptable, or omit the field until verified.\n\nAgain: this is not a periodical\/volume\/issue blocker. It is more naturally part of the upcoming date\/refinement work.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Optional: mark publication-list reviews as `Review` too\n\nOn the review page, Christian Right is:\n\n```json\n\"@type\": [\n  \"ScholarlyArticle\",\n  \"Review\"\n]\n```\n\nOn `\/publications\/`, it is only:\n\n```json\n\"@type\": \"ScholarlyArticle\"\n```\n\nFor consistency, review items on `\/publications\/` could also use:\n\n```json\n\"@type\": [\n  \"ScholarlyArticle\",\n  \"Review\"\n]\n```\n\nThis applies to the review entries generally.\n\nThis is optional. A `Review` is a kind of creative work, and the current version is not invalid. But since these are book reviews, adding `Review` is more precise.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Optional: canonicalise periodical node IDs across pages later\n\nAt present, the same Christian Right issue is represented with different local IDs on different pages:\n\nOn `\/publications\/`:\n\n```text\nhttps:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/publications\/#review-christian-right-europe-issue\n```\n\nOn the review page:\n\n```text\nhttps:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/publications\/reviews\/christian-right-europe\/#issue\n```\n\nThis is acceptable because each page has its own JSON-LD graph. But if you wanted stronger cross-page consistency, you could have the publications page point to the review page’s canonical rich nodes for entries that have dedicated review pages:\n\n```text\nhttps:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/publications\/reviews\/christian-right-europe\/#issue\nhttps:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/publications\/reviews\/christian-right-europe\/#volume\nhttps:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/publications\/reviews\/christian-right-europe\/#periodical\n```\n\nI would not treat this as necessary now. The current approach is fine for Stage 3.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Specific note on Cosmic Connections\n\nThis part looks reasonable:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"@id\": \"https:\/\/doi.org\/10.1177\/13684310241249684\",\n  \"@type\": \"ScholarlyArticle\",\n  \"isPartOf\": {\n    \"@id\": \"https:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/publications\/#review-cosmic-connections-issue\"\n  },\n  \"pagination\": \"339–42\",\n  \"pageStart\": \"339\",\n  \"pageEnd\": \"342\"\n}\n```\n\nThe periodical chain also looks structurally fine:\n\n```text\nEuropean Journal of Social Theory\n  volume 28\n    issue 2\n```\n\nThe main correction there is the date-time precision:\n\n```json\n\"datePublished\": \"2024-05-24T12:00:00+01:00\"\n```\n\nshould probably become:\n\n```json\n\"datePublished\": \"2024-05-24\"\n```\n\nunless that exact time is genuinely meaningful.\n\n---\n\n## Recommendation\n\nYou can mark the **“add periodical\/volume\/issue nodes”** task as done, or done with minor follow-up notes.\n\nBefore moving to `firstPublishedOnline`, I would make just one quick fix if convenient:\n\n1. Add the Christian Right `Article ID` identifier to the review-page DOI node, matching `\/publications\/`.\n\nThen move on.\n\nI would track the rest under date\/metadata cleanup rather than keeping the periodical\/volume\/issue task open:\n\n- verify or reduce issue-level `datePublished`;\n- add `firstPublishedOnline`;\n- remove invented datetime \/ Jan 1 dates;\n- update old `Dr Stevan Veljkovic` schema strings;\n- optionally add `Review` to publication-list review item types;\n- optionally canonicalise periodical node IDs across pages later.","refusal":null,"role":"assistant"},{"content":"26 May 2026 at 14:53:46 BST\n\n# Further JSON-LD Validation\n\nThis is now the JSON-LD from the christian-right-europe review page:\n\n```json\n{\n      \"@context\": \"https:\/\/schema.org\",\n      \"@graph\": [\n        {\n          \"@id\": \"https:\/\/orcid.org\/0000-0002-2599-3227\",\n          \"@type\": \"Person\",\n          \"name\": \"Stevan Veljkovic\",\n          \"url\": \"https:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/\",\n          \"identifier\": {\n            \"@type\": \"PropertyValue\",\n            \"propertyID\": \"ORCID\",\n            \"value\": \"0000-0002-2599-3227\",\n            \"url\": \"https:\/\/orcid.org\/0000-0002-2599-3227\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"@id\": \"https:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/#website\",\n          \"@type\": \"WebSite\",\n          \"url\": \"https:\/\/stevanveljkovic.com\/\",\n          \"name\": \"Stevan Veljkovic\",\n          \"inLanguage\": \"en-GB\",\n          \"publisher\": {\n            \"@id\": \"https:\/\/orcid.org\/0000-0002-2599-3227